itary motorcycles mostly wlas and wlcs the canadian version were produced many to be provided to allies harleydavidson received two armynavy ‘e’ awards one in  and the other in  which were awarded for excellence in production harley produced the wlc for the canadian military shipments to the soviet union under the lendlease program numbered at least  the wlas produced during all four years of war production generally have  serial numbers production of the wla stopped at the end of world war ii but was resumed from  to  for use in the korean war the us army also asked harleydavidson to produce a new motorcycle with many of the features of bmws sidevalve and shaftdriven r harley largely copied the bmw engine and drive train and produced the shaftdriven  cc  harleydavidson xa this shared no dimensions no parts and no design concepts except side valves with any prior harleydavidson engine due to the superior cooling of the flattwin engine with the cylinders across the frame harleys xa cylinder heads ran  °f  °c cooler than its vtwins the xa never entered full production the motorcycle by that time had been eclipsed by the jeep as the armys general purpose vehicle and the wla—already in production—was sufficient for its limited police escort and courier roles only  were made and the xa never went into full production it remains the only shaftdriven harleydavidson ever made small harleys hummers and aermacchis harleydavidson hummer see also harleydavidson hummer and harleydavidson topper as part of war reparations harleydavidson acquired the design of a small german motorcycle the dkw rt  which they adapted manufactured and sold from  to  various models were made including the hummer from  to  but they are all colloquially referred to as hummers at present bsa in the united kingdom took the same design as the foundation of their bsa bantam  aermacchi harleydavidson turismo veloce in  harleydavidson consolidated the model  and hummer lines into the super introduced the top