d harleydavidson to produce a new motorcycle with many of the features of bmws sidevalve and shaftdriven r harley largely copied the bmw engine and drive train and produced the shaftdriven  cc  harleydavidson xa this shared no dimensions no parts and no design concepts except side valves with any prior harleydavidson engine due to the superior cooling of the flattwin engine with the cylinders across the frame harleys xa cylinder heads ran  °f  °c cooler than its vtwins the xa never entered full production the motorcycle by that time had been eclipsed by the jeep as the armys general purpose vehicle and the wla—already in production—was sufficient for its limited police escort and courier roles only  were made and the xa never went into full production it remains the only shaftdriven harleydavidson ever made small harleys hummers and aermacchis harleydavidson hummer see also harleydavidson hummer and harleydavidson topper as part of war reparations harleydavidson acquired the design of a small german motorcycle the dkw rt  which they adapted manufactured and sold from  to  various models were made including the hummer from  to  but they are all colloquially referred to as hummers at present bsa in the united kingdom took the same design as the foundation of their bsa bantam  aermacchi harleydavidson turismo veloce in  harleydavidson consolidated the model  and hummer lines into the super introduced the topper scooter and bought fifty percent of aermacchis motorcycle division importation of aermacchis  cc horizontal single began the following year the bike bore harleydavidson badges and was marketed as the harleydavidson sprint the engine of the sprint was increased to  cc in  and would remain that size until  when the fourstroke sprint was discontinued after the pacer and scat models were discontinued at the end of  the bobcat became the last of harleydavidsons americanmade twostroke motorcycles the bobcat was manufactured only in the  model year harleydavidson repla